[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide has passed 4 million and is 4 012 769, with reports of cases by 216 countries and territories worldwide. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 97.9% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA, with more than 1.32 million confirmed cases, now represents 32.9% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 276 216 deaths have been reported, with 271 582 (98.3%) outside mainland China.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19, Spain is number 2, and Italy is number 3, followed by the UK, Russia, France, Germany, Brazil, Turkey, and Iran as number 10. China is now number 11. Brazil has moved up from 9th to 8th place in terms of cumulative case numbers and having the 2nd highest number of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (11 201), following the USA (29 162), with Russia reporting the 3rd highest 24-hour newly confirmed cases (10 699). - Mod.MPP]

